# Issue:

Windows VM could not access the Internet

## Symptoms:

![image.png](attachment:2d50f7b9-5394-4aa5-b890-31d445d46f6d:image.png)

No default gateway present in `ipconfig /all` output

No internet in browser

ping 8.8.8.8 failed

IP address is 169.254.42.141 which means APIPA was assigned

## Root Cause Analysis

The VM was connected to a Host-Only network, which provides a local IP address but does not assign a default gateway. Without a gateway, the system cannot route traffic outside the local network.

## Why It Was Not DNS

Ping to 8.8.8.8 failed, indicating the issue was not name resolution but lack of network routing.

## Why It Was Not DHCP Failure

The system received a valid IP (192.168.56.x), meaning DHCP was functioning within the Host-Only network.

## Network Layer Breakdown

- IP Address: Present ✅
- Gateway: Missing ❌
- DNS: Irrelevant due to no routing ❌

## Steps Taken

1. Ran ipconfig → saw APIPA address (169.254.42.141)
2. Tested connectivity with ping → failed
3. Checked VirtualBox network settings
4. Found adapter set to Host-Only instead of NAT

![image.png](attachment:3e567061-a9cf-4544-9224-ad8b9deb424b:image.png)

Noticed the network Adapter was set to Host-only Adapter

## ✅ Resolution

Changed network adapter back to NAT → renewed IP → internet restored

![image.png](attachment:56da81cb-8af3-4261-bdc7-b13335975191:image.png)

Did inconfig /release > ipconfig /renew > gateway established>Connection to internet restore

## Key Concepts

- APIPA (169.254.x.x)
- DHCP failure
- VirtualBox network modes (NAT vs Host-Only)

# 🚨 What I Learned

A valid IP address does not guarantee internet access. The absence of a default gateway prevents routing beyond the local network.
